news.title: Bengaluru: BDA to ask agency to check Nadaprabhu Kempegowda layout work
news.para: Looking into various petitions filed by legislators and citizens, the petition committee of the state legislature held a preliminary meeting with BDA officials on May 5.

news.title: Chandigarh housing board earns Rs 2 crore from four properties
news.para: The board had put total 35 freehold properties, including 29 residential and six commercial properties, for auction. The board found buyers for two EWS flats in sectors 40 and 52, selling them for Rs 22.5 lakh and Rs 24.5 lakh.

news.title: Nod for amnesty scheme to revive 380 'dead' slum redevelopment projects in Mumbai
news.para: Under the scheme, financial institutions (FIs) like non-banking financial companies and other firms that have invested in SRA projects that have been stalled will be able to resume redevelopment without any major penalty and even get easy clearances.

news.title: Kolkata: Stability focus on over 150 Bowbazar buildings
news.para: “On identifying the most unstable structures, the JU team will desist from directly recommending razing. Instead, they will refer to the buildings’ lime-mortar character and seek specialized restoration or meticulous stitching of the structures,” said a source.

news.title: Shalimar Paints' net loss declines to Rs 13 crore in Q4 FY22
news.para: Its revenue from operations was down by 5.55 per cent at Rs 105.54 crore during the quarter under review as against Rs 111.74 crore in the year-ago period.

news.title: NGT needs to broaden proceedings against illegal sand-mining across Meghalaya: HC
news.para: ​A full bench headed by Chief Justice Sanjib Banerjee was on Tuesday hearing a suo motu petition filed by the registrar general of the high court following reports of unregulated sand-mining destroying water bodies across the state.

news.title: Thane: Court rejects pre-arrest bail plea of builder accused of cheating buyers
news.para: According to the victims, the partners of Chaitanya Builders and Developers at Mira Road had taken money from them for tenements, but had not given them flats and cheated them.

news.title: Slum-dwellers are citizens too, have a right to life: Punjab & Haryana HC
news.para: A bench of justice Amol Rattan Singh and justice Lalit Batra acted on the plea of Rajinder Kumar and others seeking quashing of the May 14 demolition notices put up by the UT administration.

news.title: About 50% of residential complexes in Bengaluru are green: Study
news.para: The assessment, said to be the first of its kind in Bengaluru, was carried out by the pollution watchdog after analysing 95 large apartments on over 15 green building-related parameters.

news.title: Hyderabad's early bird property taxpayers face online glitches
news.para: Residents have been forced to repeatedly visit local GHMC offices and banks to rectify instances of payment glitches.

news.title: Jaipur: Amrit Kunj owners get plots in new scheme after 12 years
news.para: The Jaipur Development Authority (JDA) has allotted plots to successful allottees in another scheme named Amirt Kunj-2 in zone-12.

news.title: Homes delivered but no power connection: Vipul World buyers
news.para: DHBVN stopped providing new electricity connections to 16 societies in July last year for non-payment of charges for developing power infrastructure by developers. DHBVN had to recover Rs 317 crore from the developers of these colonies.

news.title: Promoters' stake in Aurum PropTech rises to 50.34% post rights-issue
news.para: “This fresh infusion of capital will further institutionalise adoption of technology in the real estate sector,” said Ashish Deora, Founder and Chief Executive Officer of Aurum Ventures, the holding company of Aurum PropTech.

news.title: Phoenix Mills to add 4.4 million sq ft to retail portfolio in 12-15 months
news.para: Phoenix that counts Singapore sovereign wealth fund GIC and the Canada Pension Plan Investment Board (CPPIB) as its partners will hold around 4.4 million sq ft cumulative leasable retail space across the four malls. The company is investing around Rs 4,000 crore to develop the retail component of these projects.

news.title: Phoenix Mills' net profit jumps 101%, income up 28% in FY22
news.para: Operating profit for the quarter rose 39% to Rs 241 crore and Rs 734 crore for the financial year, up 49%.
